Payments & checkout

Payment methods

Tap, dip, or swipe
Tap, dip, or swipe

Accept payments with tap, chip, or swipe functionality. Cards and digital wallets included.

Tap to Pay on iPhone and Tap to Pay on Android
Tap to Pay on iPhone and Tap to Pay on Android

Take payments with just your phone. Accept contactless cards, Apple Pay, and other digital wallets in person. No additional hardware needed.

Manual entry or card on file
Manual entry or card on file

Manually enter a customer's card details or securely add cards to customer profiles and use at checkout.

ACH bank transfers
ACH bank transfers

Let customers pay directly from their bank account with a secure invoice. Customers can pay via ACH with just their bank account and routing number.

Afterpay
Afterpay

Let customers pay in four interest-free installments over six weeks. You'll receive the full payment up front.

Cash App Pay
Cash App Pay

Allow customers to pay with Cash App Pay by scanning a QR code.

Checkout

Discounts and refunds
Discounts and refunds

Create percentage or dollar amount discounts. Issue full or partial refunds to the original payment or as store credit.

Age verification prompts
Age verification prompts

Set age restrictions on items like alcohol and tobacco and verify the age of customers at checkout.

Bottle deposits
Bottle deposits

Set up a bottle deposit per item, and it’ll be added to the order at time of checkout automatically.

Exchanges
Exchanges

Process a product exchange for your customer.

Cross-location returns and fulfillment
Cross-location returns and fulfillment

Accept returns at any location, regardless of where the purchase was made.

Restaurant operations

Menus, coursing, and floor plans

Item and menu management
Item and menu management

Update your on-premise and online menus in real time and sync changes to all locations and channels — POS, online, kiosks, and delivery apps. Use bulk edits to quickly manage item availability or visibility.

Third-party order management
Third-party order management

Consolidate all your online menus and orders, including those from delivery partners like Grubhub and Door Dash, in one platform. Sort by order status and source.

Custom floor plans
Custom floor plans

Customize your restaurant floor plan with click-and-drag layouts. Use color-coded labels to show if a table has been waiting too long.

Item availability
Item availability

Mark items as sold out in real time across every sales channel to keep your team on the same page.

Advanced modifiers
Advanced modifiers

Capture complex orders easily. With step-by-step flows, quantity controls, and smart sequencing for things like toppings or sides, you reduce mistakes and speed up service. Available for Square for Franchises.

Order guide
Order guide

See vendor prices side-by-side and compare costs per unit in real time. You can also turn your menu into an ingredients list instantly. This feature is currently in beta, but you can still use it while we add the finishing touches.

Bulk edit items in menus
Bulk edit items in menus

Update multiple items using the bulk editing tool from Square Dashboard to easily make changes to your menu at scale.

Seat management
Seat management

Add a cover count to your tables, including optional or required seat positions for dishes, so your staff knows where to deliver each dish.

Course management
Course management

Organize checks and kitchen tickets so items are prepared and served at the right time. Customize course settings for each device.

Reservation integrations
Reservation integrations

Take reservations by integrating your system with apps like OpenTable and SevenRooms.

Payments, discounts, and gratuity

Automatic gratuity
Automatic gratuity

Add a fixed-percentage gratuity to your customer’s check, manually or automatically. Add gratuity based on party size.

Simple percentage
Party-size thresholds
Party-size thresholds
Service charges
Service charges

Add a percentage-based or fixed-amount service charge to a transaction to help offset operational or overhead costs. Visible as a line item to both you and your customer.

Instant payouts
Instant payouts

Get real-time access to earnings from online marketplace and ordering platforms in your Square Checking account.

Checks

Orders tab
Orders tab

Manage all your on-premise and online orders, including delivery-partner sites such as DoorDash, in one place. Filter by order status and source.

Open checks and house accounts
Open checks and house accounts

Create, edit, and save an order before completing the sale. Create and manage customer accounts to keep a running balance of purchases, then send an invoice when it's time to pay.

QR code payments
QR code payments

Enable QR code payments on receipts to speed up table turnover and free up staff time.

Order-ready texts
Order-ready texts

Collect a guest’s phone number to automatically send a text when their order is marked as complete in KDS.

Split or reopen checks
Split or reopen checks

Split a check by items or seats, or split an amount into equal payments. Reopen a check to adjust and comp or void items, then choose to keep the original payment method or refund the customer.

Preauthorize bar tabs
Preauthorize bar tabs

Temporarily preauthorize a customer's credit card for a set amount to ensure it's valid and they can pay the bill when closing their tab.

Take orders tableside
Take orders tableside

Device settings

Remote device management
Remote device management

Set up, monitor, and manage devices, even when you’re off-site. View device details, set device profiles or codes, and create printer profiles.

Bookings

Scheduling

Unlimited calendars
Unlimited calendars

Add and view as many staff calendars as your business needs. There is no employee limit.

Custom scheduling
Custom scheduling

Customize your calendar based on your availability. Color code your schedule by staff or by service, set a daily appointment limit, and block off personal time.

Online booking website and booking integrations
Online booking website and booking integrations

Create and customize a booking website so clients can book 24/7. Add a Book Now button to your website, create a QR code for a contactless booking option, or embed a booking widget into an existing website.

Prepayments and automatic contracts
Prepayments and automatic contracts

Require your clients to pay in advance for specific services or as part of your cancellation policy. Send contracts to clients automatically when they book.

Appointment deposits
Appointment deposits

Collect a partial deposit when appointments are scheduled to protect your calendar and reduce no-shows.

Digital wallets in booking flow
Digital wallets in booking flow

Let clients check out with the wallets they already use — like Apple Pay and Google Pay — during the your online booking flow so it's easier to lock in appointments on the spot.

Processing time
Processing time

Account for downtime for certain services, such as hair-color treatments, and let clients book during the downtime of existing appointments.

Multi-staff appointment booking
Multi-staff appointment booking

Let clients book one appointment with multiple services assigned to different staff.

Cancellation policy and no-show fees
Cancellation policy and no-show fees

Set up time frames for cancellations and require customers to provide a credit card at booking. Charge the card on file for late cancellations or no-shows.

Daily booking limit
Daily booking limit

Set a booking cap for online customers. Allow team members to book above the threshold if needed.

Class booking and packages
Class booking and packages

Offer a prepaid series of services or classes, automatically applying the booking's value at checkout when customers redeem them. Create and schedule one-time or recurring group classes.

Multi-location management
Multi-location management

Manage your calendar, staff, and online bookings across multiple locations.

Waitlist
Waitlist

Create a waitlist for popular services and staff. Let clients join the waitlist through your booking site and receive notifications when an appointment opens up.

Resource management
Resource management

Assign rooms, chairs, stations, and other resources to the services required.

Client communication

Appointment reminders
Appointment reminders

Set up automatic text and email reminder notifications to help clients manage their appointments.

Custom notifications
Custom notifications

Customize text and email notifications to fit your brand.

Custom emails
Custom emails & texts
Custom emails & texts
Square Assistant
Square Assistant

Let customers respond directly to SMS appointment reminders to confirm, cancel, or change their appointment. Your calendar updates automatically with every change.

Appointment confirmations
Appointment confirmations

Send clients text and email confirmations. Confirmed appointments will appear in your calendar.

Integrations

Instagram, Facebook, and Google integrations
Instagram, Facebook, and Google integrations

Add a Book Now button to your Instagram account, your Facebook page, or your Google Business Profile.

Google Calendar sync
Google Calendar sync

Sync your Square calendar with your Google Calendar to track bookings.

Bookings API
Bookings API

Use the Booking API to allow an external application to create, update, and cancel every booking from your calendar.

Inventory & catalog management

Item management

Automatically create items and SKUs
Automatically create items and SKUs

Search or scan a GTIN barcode to automatically add items to your catalog or import your existing catalog in bulk. Automatically populate SKUs for future items that you create and generate missing SKUs for existing items. Create new items with auto-generated SKUs.

Auto-polish item image
Auto-polish item image

Create professional-looking product images right from your POS. Auto-polish instantly removes backgrounds so your products stand out — no photo editing needed.

Inventory tracking
Inventory tracking

Track stock, costs, and product availability. Monitor inventory levels to maximize profitability and ensure adequate supply.

Product bundles
Product bundles

Sell a combination of complementary products as a single unit.

Inventory management

Low-stock alerts
Low-stock alerts

Set an alert for when stock counts dip below a certain quantity so you can get ahead of knowing when it’s time to restock.

Barcode label printing
Barcode label printing

Create and print barcode labels using the supported label dimensions, printing templates, and printers.

Manage unit costs
Manage unit costs

Produce more detailed reports, like cost of goods sold, and better calculate margins with the ability to add unit costs to items in the catalog.

Inventory history
Inventory history

Get a detailed view of your current inventory levels by listing out each stock adjustment.

Inventory counting tool
Inventory counting tool

Perform full or cycle counts on the go. Export counts to reconcile stock on hand with expected inventory and maintain accurate records.

Vendor and purchase order management
Vendor and purchase order management

Create vendor profiles to use when making barcodes, purchase orders, and reports. Manage purchase orders for every vendor.

Bulk inventory intake
Bulk inventory intake

Quickly receive stock in bulk by scanning or by searching for items.

Import purchase orders
Import purchase orders

Create purchase orders by importing a CSV or Excel version of the purchase order.

Transfer orders
Transfer orders

Create and track inventory transfers across locations in stages: draft, pending, partially received, and completed.

Sync with Shopify using Thrive
Sync with Shopify using Thrive

With Thrive Inventory, you can sync your Square catalog and inventory with Shopify, so you can sell in-store and online while managing products in one place. Keep Square as your source of truth to cut down on manual work.

Square Restaurant Inventory by MarketMan
Square Restaurant Inventory by MarketMan

Sync your menu to track ingredient-level stock and reduce waste — without adding complexity to your team’s workflow. Pricing applicable for customers new to MarketMan.

$99/mo. per location
$99/mo. per location

Reporting & analytics

Sales reporting

Sales insights
Sales insights

Select a date range to track a sales summary, including payments and fees. Check trends by item, category, timeframe, location, and more.

Reconciliation report
Reconciliation report

The reconciliation report breaks down sales, refunds, fees, and deposits — so you know where your money's going.

Custom work week
Custom work week

Set your business week to start on any day — not just Monday — so your sales and labor reports align with your actual shifts. Great for businesses that close on Mondays or run unique schedules.

Daily sales summary email
Daily sales summary email

Get a quick snapshot of your sales from the previous day in your inbox every morning — with wide-ranging metrics to help you understand your performance. This feature is rolling out in phases and will appear in your Square account automatically. If you don’t see it yet, hang tight — access is on the way.

Bookings reporting

Future bookings report
Future bookings report

Get insights into future earnings from booked appointments.

Service cost tracking
Service cost tracking

Manage back bar expenses with detailed cost tracking for each service.

Team performance report
Team performance report

Measure team performance with metrics on retention, prebooking, and schedule utilization.

Inventory reporting

Aging inventory report

Track inventory aging to identify slow-moving stock, optimize restocking, and reduce waste.

Cost of goods sold report
Cost of goods sold report

Keep an eye on topline metrics like cost of goods, total revenue, profit, and profit margin.

Inventory sell-through report
Inventory sell-through report

Get a daily snapshot of all the information you need to manage your inventory effectively.

Projected profit report
Projected profit report

Break your data into smaller sections to see the performance of an item, view each location’s profit potential, and see how each inventory category is contributing to your business.

Vendor sales
Vendor sales

Marketing reporting

Marketing reports
Marketing reports

Track campaign success, customer engagement, and sales impact.

Restaurant reporting

Deferred sales tracking
Deferred sales tracking

Catalog reporting
Catalog reporting

See how your full menu is performing and consolidate item performance across sales from seven different sources, such as POS, online, delivery apps, and more, into a single flexible report.

Live section and shift reporting
Live section and shift reporting

Get details about open checks, closed checks, and total sales. See the sales numbers for each part of the restaurant, including bar, dining room, or patio. View covers and total sales at any given moment.

Close of day procedures and reporting
Close of day procedures and reporting

Run close of day and team member shift reports to see daily sales activity and team member tip payouts. Check details, gross and net sales, payment methods, and category and item sales.

Menu reports
Menu reports

Filter reports by menu. For example, compare dinner versus lunch or lunch versus happy hour.

Kitchen performance reporting
Kitchen performance reporting

See completed ticket count and average completed ticket time across all devices and locations.

Invoices reporting

Invoices reporting
Invoices reporting

Track the status of invoices in real time to see what's paid, unpaid, and overdue.

Staff reporting

Team sales and activity reporting
Team sales and activity reporting

See who's making the most sales on your team and view all team activity at your POS. Track who issued refunds, when employees clocked in, and more.

Labor cost reporting
Labor cost reporting

Compare your hourly labor costs to net sales to make smarter staffing decisions. Forecast total labor expenses for upcoming schedules.

Web reporting

Site and eCommerce data
Site and eCommerce data

Track the number of visitors to your site, which pages are most visited, and more. See sales trends, product performance, and voucher usage.

Square AI

Chat with Square AI to get business recommendations based on your data, industry trends, and web search. Square AI can also suggest new Square features so you get more out of our tools. This feature is currenty in beta, but you can still use it while we add the finishing touches.

FAQ

  • Is there a free trial and can I cancel later?

    Square Plus and Square Premium each offer a free 30-day trial, and you can cancel or switch plans anytime. With Square Free, there are no monthly subscription costs — you only pay processing fees when you take a payment.

  • How much will I pay in processing fees?

    Processing fees vary based on the Square plan you choose. Square Premium offers the lowest processing fees. If you process over $250,000 per year, you can talk to our team about custom pricing and processing fees.

    Learn more about our fees

  • Can I accept any type of credit card?

    You can accept every major card — Visa, Mastercard, American Express, and Discover — all for the same processing fees. You can also take cash, checks, and Square Gift Cards.

  • When will I get paid?

    You can transfer funds to an external bank account the next business day for free or instantly for a fee.

    Learn more

  • Do I need to purchase hardware?

    You do not need to purchase hardware to take payments with Square. There are several ways to take payments without any hardware, including invoicing, payment links, virtual terminal, Tap to Pay on iPhone, and Tap to Pay on Android.

  • How can I get in touch for support?

    You can contact sales for support getting started or with your account.

  • How can I switch from my current solution?

    With Square you can get set up quickly. Import existing customer contacts and connect third–party apps you already use.

  • I already use Square. Has my pricing changed?

    If you're already using Square, your pricing may change depending on your current plan. We'll notify you ahead of time so you know exactly what to expect.

    These changes are designed to make Square's pricing simpler and give you more flexibility.

    Learn about changes to Square plans
